        "text": "**Key Differentiators:**\n* **igus drylin:** Uses sliding contact with self-lubricating polymer liners. It operates completely dry without grease or oil, making it maintenance-free and highly resistant to dirt and dust. \n* **THK:** Uses recirculating ball bearings (rolling contact). They offer superior precision, rigidity, and load capacity but require continuous lubrication. In dusty settings, debris can mix with the grease and jam the bearing unless specialized contamination protection (like THK's LaCS scrapers) is utilized.\n\n**Recommendation for Woodworking:**\n**igus drylin** is highly recommended for a dusty woodworking environment. Because it runs completely dry, sawdust and wood chips cannot stick to the rails or clump into an abrasive paste. The polymer liners simply wipe the dust away, ensuring reliable operation without the heavy maintenance overhead of recirculating ball guides.\n\n**Orderable Part Examples (igus drylin W series):**\n* **Guide Rail:** `WS-10-40-1000` (1000mm Double Guide Rail, 10mm shaft diameter)\n* **Carriage Block:** `WJ200UM-01` (Standard pillow block carriage with iglide® J200 sliding elements)",
